00:27.804 --> 00:29.672
Oh. Sorry I'm late.

00:29.673 --> 00:31.940
Bit of a hectic morning.

00:33.510 --> 00:36.379
Although, sometimes when,
uh, people are in conflict

00:36.380 --> 00:38.381
and they're left alone together,

00:38.382 --> 00:42.017
they tend to work
things out themselves.

00:44.321 --> 00:46.422
Okeydoke.
Let's jump right in, then.

00:46.423 --> 00:48.891
Uh, I understand
there's some tension

00:48.892 --> 00:50.326
between the two of you.

00:50.327 --> 00:53.495
Uh, Biggs, you want to tell us
what's the matter?

00:53.497 --> 00:55.131
Actually, why don't you
let her talk first?

00:55.132 --> 00:57.799
You'll find out what
the problem is pretty quick.

00:58.669 --> 01:00.169
I didn't come here
to be insulted.

01:00.170 --> 01:01.270
I came to be vindicated.

01:01.271 --> 01:03.706
So you know what?
I will start.

01:03.707 --> 01:05.840
You know why this
relationship went wrong?

01:05.842 --> 01:07.009
'Cause my supposed best friend

01:07.010 --> 01:09.110
turned his back on me
in my time of need.

01:09.112 --> 01:12.614
Your entire life
is a time of need.

01:12.616 --> 01:13.749
See what he does?

01:13.750 --> 01:15.351
Just pecks away at
my self-esteem.

01:15.352 --> 01:17.953
Then I start thinking
that I'm the problem.

01:19.823 --> 01:21.257
You are the problem.

01:21.258 --> 01:22.557
Okay, okay.

01:22.559 --> 01:25.927
Now, Biggs, I'm hearing
a lot of anger from you.

01:25.929 --> 01:28.630
See? You're the problem.
Check and mate.

01:28.632 --> 01:29.664
No, we're not done here yet.

01:29.666 --> 01:31.099
All right, then just check.

01:32.436 --> 01:35.004
Look, I was ready
to put all this behind us

01:35.005 --> 01:37.940
until he bailed on me
and requested a new partner.

01:37.941 --> 01:40.042
Well, that's because
you bailed on me as a friend.

01:40.043 --> 01:41.943
Time after time,
you put everyone else first.

01:41.945 --> 01:43.612
Hey, I was a great friend.

01:43.614 --> 01:45.814
Until you weren't.

01:49.753 --> 01:53.355
Carl, what do you want from me?

01:53.357 --> 01:55.924
An apology would be nice.

01:57.361 --> 02:00.595
You made me feel
like I was nothing to you.

02:03.233 --> 02:05.201
Okay, fine.

02:05.202 --> 02:10.271
Carl, if I made you
feel that way, I'm sorry.

02:16.647 --> 02:18.079
Apology not accepted.

02:18.081 --> 02:19.948
What?!

02:19.950 --> 02:22.050
Well, I got what I want.
You admitted you were wrong.

02:22.052 --> 02:23.184
I didn't admit anything!

02:23.186 --> 02:24.320
Well, then why'd you apologize?

02:24.321 --> 02:25.655
Your Honor, I rest my case.

02:25.656 --> 02:27.956
And let the record show
that he can kiss my ass!

02:30.093 --> 02:33.496
Boy, he is a bit
of a drama queen, isn't he?

02:33.497 --> 02:35.864
Why couldn't you say
that when he was in here?

02:35.866 --> 02:37.599
I don't like conflict.

