03:13.859 --> 03:16.594
Mom, please close your robe.

03:16.595 --> 03:18.162
Oh, relax.

03:18.163 --> 03:20.197
I was just saying hi
to the new neighbors.

03:20.198 --> 03:21.732
Look, Peggy,
we wrote a book.

03:21.733 --> 03:23.734
We have to publicize it.

03:23.735 --> 03:26.736
You can't just keep
blowing me off.

03:27.572 --> 03:29.307
Uh-huh.

03:29.308 --> 03:30.775
Now, I may not be
that religious,

03:30.776 --> 03:33.844
but I happen to know there's
no such thing as Ash Monday.

03:33.845 --> 03:36.247
Okay.
Radio station, tomorrow.

03:36.248 --> 03:37.782
Just be there.

03:37.783 --> 03:39.617
She's not gonna be there.

03:39.618 --> 03:41.152
Who cares?

03:41.153 --> 03:43.054
Just do the interview yourself.

03:43.055 --> 03:45.089
I can't. It's her story.

03:45.090 --> 03:47.258
Which you had to listen to
hour after hour

03:47.259 --> 03:48.626
and somehow make sense of.

03:48.627 --> 03:50.695
Yeah, you've earned
this spotlight.

03:50.696 --> 03:52.930
She may have been abused
by an alcoholic father

03:52.931 --> 03:56.533
on a run-down farm,
but you're the one who suffered.

03:57.369 --> 03:59.403
You know, you're not wrong.

03:59.404 --> 04:01.605
Sometimes with Peggy,
less is more.

04:01.606 --> 04:03.541
I mean, she's like
the shark in <i> Jaws.</i>

04:03.542 --> 04:05.543
Or at least that's
the music I hear

04:05.544 --> 04:07.944
when she's coming toward me.

04:09.581 --> 04:12.682
Why are all the neighbor kids
standing on the lawn?

04:15.087 --> 04:17.253
They're perverts.

04:18.757 --> 04:20.458
How'd it go with Carl?

04:20.459 --> 04:21.625
Total waste of time.

04:21.625 --> 04:24.061
I don't know
what I ever saw in Carl.

04:24.062 --> 04:26.529
Preach.
Right?

04:26.531 --> 04:30.033
I mean, what kind of person
doesn't accept an apology?

04:30.035 --> 04:32.103
The same kind of person
that likes to watch you

04:32.104 --> 04:34.038
pop balloons with nothing
on but high heels.

04:34.039 --> 04:35.338
Okay.

04:35.340 --> 04:38.442
You have... you have
different Carl issues.

04:38.443 --> 04:40.077
No.

04:40.078 --> 04:41.245
No, she doesn't.

04:41.246 --> 04:44.447
He's selfish
as a lover and a friend.

04:44.449 --> 04:47.418
Okay, come on. You know you guys
are gonna work it out.

04:47.419 --> 04:49.353
And if it doesn't happen
in therapy,

04:49.354 --> 04:51.455
just grab a bag of balloons.

04:51.456 --> 04:53.290
You know what he likes.

04:53.291 --> 04:54.859
That's very funny.

04:54.860 --> 04:56.160
But I don't need him anymore

04:56.161 --> 04:58.294
because I got my best friend
right here.

04:58.296 --> 04:59.397
Aw.
Mwah!

04:59.398 --> 05:00.331
My pal!

05:00.332 --> 05:01.966
Best buddies, huh?

05:03.402 --> 05:04.802
Yeah.

05:04.803 --> 05:07.505
That has got to stop.

05:07.506 --> 05:09.073
What?

05:09.074 --> 05:10.508
I-I can't keep doing
this best-friend thing.

05:10.509 --> 05:12.676
The other day,
he called me "dude."

05:12.677 --> 05:14.210
Was it during...?

05:14.212 --> 05:17.580
It was right after
but before the high five.

05:19.684 --> 05:21.951
♪ ♪

05:24.389 --> 05:27.023
I thought you can't smoke
in bars anymore.

05:27.025 --> 05:29.059
It's a cop bar.
You can do what you want.

05:29.060 --> 05:30.795
Laws do not apply.

05:30.796 --> 05:32.263
So everybody in here is a cop?

05:32.264 --> 05:33.364
Yeah, pretty much.

05:33.365 --> 05:35.800
I mean, it's a place
where we can unwind,

05:35.801 --> 05:38.536
let our guard down
and just be with our own.

05:38.537 --> 05:40.204
Like a gay bar.

05:40.205 --> 05:42.606
No. Are you kidding?

05:42.607 --> 05:43.941
There's nothing gay
about these guys.

05:43.942 --> 05:45.843
I mean, just look at all
the leather jackets

05:45.844 --> 05:47.644
and the mustaches.

05:48.513 --> 05:50.613
My mistake.

05:51.550 --> 05:53.984
Boy, ten years I tied myself
to that jackass.

05:53.985 --> 05:56.053
You know I put off
taking the sergeant's exam

05:56.054 --> 05:57.588
so I wouldn't leave Carl behind?

05:57.589 --> 06:00.324
Who knows where I'd be
if I never met him, you know?

06:00.325 --> 06:02.526
Sergeant? Lieutenant? Captain?

06:02.527 --> 06:03.994
So you gonna shoot for that now?

06:03.995 --> 06:05.196
Ah, it's too late.

06:05.197 --> 06:07.163
He took my youth.

06:08.800 --> 06:10.835
Uh-oh.
Speak of the devil.

06:10.836 --> 06:12.269
Oh, unbelievable.

06:12.270 --> 06:13.337
You want to take off?

06:13.338 --> 06:15.773
I got as much right
to be here as he has.

06:15.774 --> 06:16.841
Hey, Mike.

06:16.842 --> 06:18.042
Samuel.

06:18.043 --> 06:19.543
I thought we agreed...

06:19.544 --> 06:21.545
you get the diner,
I get The Nightstick.

06:21.546 --> 06:22.613
Nightstick?

06:22.614 --> 06:24.814
And you're sure
this isn't a gay bar?

06:26.051 --> 06:27.218
No big deal either way.

06:27.219 --> 06:29.520
I just like to know
before I go to the john.

06:29.521 --> 06:31.088
Look, I'm not gonna be told

06:31.089 --> 06:33.723
where I can and cannot go
in this city. Oh, yeah?

06:33.725 --> 06:35.159
Well, that's too bad,
'cause I got

06:35.160 --> 06:36.593
one more suggestion
where you can go.

06:36.595 --> 06:38.062
Oh, I was already
in that hell...

06:38.063 --> 06:39.964
for ten years, sitting
in our squad car.

06:39.965 --> 06:42.433
I'm sorry the captain ever
forced me to ride with you.

06:42.434 --> 06:44.201
What are you talking about?

06:44.202 --> 06:45.669
Nobody else wanted
any part of you,

06:45.670 --> 06:47.271
because you're
an annoying motormouth

06:47.272 --> 06:48.472
that nobody can stand.

06:48.473 --> 06:50.341
You weren't a partner;
You were a punishment.

06:50.342 --> 06:51.742
Okay, okay.

06:51.743 --> 06:53.944
Let's relax. Have a drink.

06:53.945 --> 06:56.814
If-if you want to smoke,
I can bum a cigarette

06:56.815 --> 06:59.083
off Freddie Mercury over here.

06:59.084 --> 07:01.452
You call yourself
a police officer?

07:01.453 --> 07:03.454
Look at you.
You're sloppy.

07:03.455 --> 07:05.555
You're out of shape.

07:05.557 --> 07:07.625
You're a danger to anybody
that's partnered up with you.

07:07.626 --> 07:09.192
You're not a cop;
You're a liability.

07:09.194 --> 07:11.295
All right, we're done.
No, I'll say when we're done,

07:11.296 --> 07:12.897
and we're done.
I said it first.

07:12.898 --> 07:14.898
Well, I meant it more.

07:20.438 --> 07:21.672
Whew.

07:21.673 --> 07:23.407
I've never been
to a gay bar before.

07:23.408 --> 07:25.542
It's nice, right?

07:27.812 --> 07:30.079
♪ ♪

07:31.683 --> 07:34.451
Welcome to <i> Novel Thoughts</i>

07:34.452 --> 07:37.354
with Allison Gutierrez-Cohen.

07:37.355 --> 07:40.490
I'm Allison Gutierrez-Cohen.

07:41.893 --> 07:43.694
<i>Under the Shadow of the Mountain</i>

07:43.695 --> 07:46.764
is an unflinching memoir
of Peggy Biggs,

07:46.765 --> 07:48.999
a spirited farm girl

07:49.000 --> 07:50.801
who uses love to escape

07:50.802 --> 07:53.203
the abusive bonds of her father.

07:53.204 --> 07:57.206
Unfortunately, Peggy Biggs
couldn't be with us.

07:57.208 --> 08:01.144
So, sitting in
is co-author Molly Flynn.

08:02.314 --> 08:03.914
Welcome, Molly.

08:03.915 --> 08:07.251
Hello, Allison.

08:07.252 --> 08:09.053
It is a plea-sure

08:09.054 --> 08:11.254
to be here.

08:12.190 --> 08:13.891
In the book...
Yes.

08:13.892 --> 08:16.660
...Peggy is such
a vibrant character.

08:16.661 --> 08:17.728
Mm-hmm.

08:17.729 --> 08:20.130
Being allowed
into her process...

08:20.131 --> 08:22.132
Mmm.

08:22.133 --> 08:23.934
...what a privilege.

08:23.935 --> 08:25.202
Yeah.

08:25.203 --> 08:28.439
You say privilege, I say potato.

08:35.212 --> 08:39.515
Writing has always been
intrinsic to my being.

08:39.517 --> 08:42.785
And I would hate
to be the one to say

08:42.787 --> 08:45.522
a gift given by God,

08:45.523 --> 08:48.524
but I...
I do have to thank someone.

08:51.696 --> 08:55.466
I'm sorry, what was
your question again?

08:55.467 --> 08:57.935
I didn't ask one yet.

08:57.936 --> 08:59.336
Wonderful.

08:59.337 --> 09:00.804
Wonderful...

09:00.805 --> 09:03.173
We writers are always seeking

09:03.174 --> 09:07.878
the question that has
not yet been asked.

09:07.879 --> 09:12.683
So I hope that does
answer your question.

09:12.684 --> 09:16.552
Still haven't asked one.

09:16.554 --> 09:18.722
Fantastic.

09:18.723 --> 09:20.790
Let's go to those phones.

09:22.327 --> 09:24.494
We don't take calls.

09:28.867 --> 09:30.700
May I make a call?

09:36.875 --> 09:38.208
You know, I just want to say

09:38.209 --> 09:39.877
my old partner really
did a number on me,

09:39.878 --> 09:42.179
so if I do call you Mike by
accident, don't take offense.

09:42.180 --> 09:43.413
I'm fully committed to us.

09:43.415 --> 09:45.582
Listen, why don't
we cut to the chase

09:45.583 --> 09:47.551
and deal with the elephant
in the room?

09:47.552 --> 09:48.619
What's the problem, Mike?

09:48.620 --> 09:50.988
Oh... Aw, geez.

09:50.989 --> 09:53.356
Didn't think
I'd do it that soon.

09:53.358 --> 09:56.660
Don't get me wrong,
I'm very open-minded.

09:56.661 --> 09:58.394
I like you people.

10:00.932 --> 10:03.667
I hope you're talking
about Scorpios.

10:03.668 --> 10:07.037
Whatever it is you're
calling yourselves these days.

10:07.038 --> 10:08.672
I don't mind it.

10:08.673 --> 10:10.708
Believe me, I came this close
to voting for Obama.

10:10.709 --> 10:11.874
Oh...

10:11.876 --> 10:14.143
And who doesn't love
Michael Jordan?

10:14.145 --> 10:16.547
He's one of the good ones.

10:16.548 --> 10:19.550
I mean, I don't think I want
the man living next door to me.

10:19.551 --> 10:20.818
It's not him, mind you.

10:20.819 --> 10:23.754
It's the people
he brings around.

10:23.755 --> 10:25.722
Who, Scottie Pippen?

10:25.724 --> 10:29.526
The point is I'm okay with
all this mixing of the races.

10:29.527 --> 10:31.562
As long as it's not next door.

10:31.563 --> 10:34.231
Exactly. I'm glad
we're on the same page.

10:37.168 --> 10:40.403
Ooh, that's gonna stain.

10:40.405 --> 10:42.372
Glad you weren't wearing
your white sheet.

10:42.373 --> 10:44.640
♪ ♪

10:46.845 --> 10:48.545
Oh, don't be upset
about it, honey.

10:48.546 --> 10:50.480
Nobody listens to NPR.

10:50.482 --> 10:52.783
Well, nobody I know.

10:52.784 --> 10:54.752
No, I haven't met
my new partner.

10:54.753 --> 10:56.487
From what I hear,
she's a real-deal cop.

10:56.488 --> 10:58.522
Very professional.

10:58.523 --> 11:01.158
Yes, I brought her the cookies.

11:01.159 --> 11:02.726
Yeah, but I want
to play it cool.

11:02.727 --> 11:04.762
Maybe I'll give 'em to her
around snack time.

11:04.763 --> 11:06.829
Oh, here she comes.
I got to go.

11:09.534 --> 11:10.868
Biggs.

11:10.869 --> 11:12.135
Stoltz.

11:12.137 --> 11:14.438
Listen, if this
partnership's gonna work,

11:14.439 --> 11:16.073
we got to lay down
a few ground rules.

11:16.074 --> 11:17.974
Boundaries.
I like you already.

11:18.576 --> 11:20.977
Sorry.

11:20.979 --> 11:23.313
First off,
I keep a clean vehicle.

11:23.314 --> 11:25.149
This is a squad car,
not a lunchroom.

11:25.150 --> 11:26.383
No eating.

11:26.384 --> 11:27.317
Got it.

11:27.318 --> 11:28.952
However, I do have
low blood sugar.

11:28.953 --> 11:31.321
I-I can step outside
to have my string cheese.

11:31.322 --> 11:34.792
Second, let's keep
it professional.

11:34.793 --> 11:37.928
You don't bitch about your wife,
I don't bitch about mine.

11:37.929 --> 11:39.830
You mean husband.

11:39.831 --> 11:42.132
You don't mean husband.

11:42.133 --> 11:43.934
You got a problem with that?
Nope.

11:43.935 --> 11:45.235
I'm very open-minded.

11:45.236 --> 11:47.470
Came this close
to voting for Obama.

11:48.706 --> 11:50.841
Hey, where's the shotgun?

11:50.842 --> 11:51.809
Oh, it's in the trunk.

11:51.810 --> 11:53.442
It's safer that way.
For who?

11:53.444 --> 11:55.445
The dirtbags rolling up on us?

11:55.446 --> 11:58.014
Unbelievable.

12:02.187 --> 12:03.520
Molly, it's not a good time.

12:03.521 --> 12:04.888
I'll call you at lunch.

12:04.889 --> 12:06.223
If we get a lunch.

12:06.224 --> 12:07.723
She's kind of mean.

12:11.429 --> 12:13.497
Want to secure that in
your cookie holder?

12:13.498 --> 12:16.799
I'm sorry, I did not
know the rules yet.

12:23.842 --> 12:25.209
Need some help?

12:25.210 --> 12:26.176
No, I do not.

12:26.177 --> 12:27.544
And just so we're clear,

12:27.545 --> 12:29.546
I've been on the force
a lot longer than you,

12:29.547 --> 12:31.882
and I know what I'm doing,
so don't talk down to me

12:31.883 --> 12:33.851
like I'm some rookie,
you got it?

12:33.852 --> 12:34.917
Got it.
Good.

12:43.995 --> 12:46.963
Yeah, it's, uh, still
not a good time.

12:46.965 --> 12:49.232
♪ ♪

12:57.129 --> 12:58.763
<i>Mike, you're gonna be late.</i>

12:58.764 --> 13:00.431
I'm taking a sick day.

13:00.432 --> 13:02.333
Maybe a sick month.

13:02.334 --> 13:04.402
Come on, the longer yo♪
avoid going into work,

13:04.403 --> 13:05.702
it's just gonna get worse.

13:05.704 --> 13:08.572
They're calling me
"Moonroof Mike."

13:09.908 --> 13:11.609
Oh, that's nice, real nice.

13:11.610 --> 13:13.110
What? It's cute.

13:13.111 --> 13:14.111
It means they like you.

13:14.112 --> 13:15.412
You're one of the gang.

13:15.414 --> 13:17.915
Well, most of them won't even
make eye contact with me.

13:17.916 --> 13:19.116
You know what that is?

13:19.117 --> 13:20.785
That's a sign of respect.

13:20.786 --> 13:22.853
At least it is with gorillas.

13:22.854 --> 13:24.687
Not helping.

13:27.459 --> 13:30.060
I think that somebody needs
one of my special stories.

13:30.061 --> 13:31.295
I don't, I don't.

13:31.296 --> 13:32.496
Yeah, you do.

13:32.497 --> 13:34.765
Roll over.

13:34.766 --> 13:36.434
Okay.

13:36.435 --> 13:38.469
The year was 1989.

13:38.470 --> 13:40.104
There was a young ambitious girl

13:40.105 --> 13:42.639
and a summer job at Peps Tacos.

13:42.641 --> 13:45.376
Now, was this girl the youngest
assistant manager

13:45.377 --> 13:46.977
ever to work for the franchise?

13:46.978 --> 13:48.746
Yes, she was, but that's
not what we're talking...

13:48.747 --> 13:50.448
Just tell it.
All right.

13:50.449 --> 13:52.550
I was closing up one night.

13:52.551 --> 13:54.919
I left a cup
under the soda machine.

13:54.920 --> 13:56.921
It ran until morning.

13:58.623 --> 14:00.858
Do you know what they called me?

14:00.859 --> 14:03.594
Called me "Bubbles."

14:03.595 --> 14:04.929
Did it hurt?

14:04.930 --> 14:06.297
Yeah, you bet.

14:06.298 --> 14:07.932
Okay, did I lay in bed all day?

14:07.933 --> 14:09.233
No, sirree.

14:09.234 --> 14:11.235
I got up,
and I marched in there,

14:11.236 --> 14:12.937
and I told them
that Charlene was pregnant,

14:12.938 --> 14:15.738
and they forgot all about me.

14:15.740 --> 14:18.142
Hmm? Oh,
so-so what you're saying is...

14:18.143 --> 14:22.179
you spilled some soda,
and I almost killed my partner,

14:22.180 --> 14:24.415
and that's the same thing.

14:24.416 --> 14:26.350
Okay, I tried.

14:26.351 --> 14:29.186
You're gonna stay home, you got
to do the grocery shopping.

14:29.187 --> 14:30.354
And I need tampons.

14:30.355 --> 14:32.222
Aw, dude!

14:33.091 --> 14:35.358
♪ ♪

14:37.796 --> 14:39.797
Okay, you win.

14:39.798 --> 14:42.466
I cannot do these
interviews alone.

14:42.467 --> 14:43.834
That's for damn sure.

14:43.835 --> 14:45.269
I don't know how you did it,

14:45.270 --> 14:48.304
but you managed to be
too boring for NPR.

14:48.306 --> 14:50.608
She should have
let me take callers.

14:50.609 --> 14:53.209
I need an audience
to feed off their energy.

14:53.211 --> 14:54.311
You'll get 'em next time.

14:54.312 --> 14:55.346
Or not.

14:55.347 --> 14:56.647
Who cares?

14:56.648 --> 14:57.948
What is your problem?

14:57.949 --> 15:00.084
We published a book
about your life.

15:00.085 --> 15:01.752
I mean, doesn't it mean
anything to you?

15:01.753 --> 15:03.487
It means the world to me.

15:03.488 --> 15:04.989
Well, then go out there
and talk about it.

15:04.990 --> 15:06.524
This is supposed
to be the fun part.

15:06.525 --> 15:07.992
Why can't you just enjoy it?

15:07.993 --> 15:10.094
Let me tell you how God works.

15:11.296 --> 15:14.031
He sees you loving life
a little too much,

15:14.032 --> 15:15.266
he'll find a way to humble you.

15:15.267 --> 15:17.368
Might be a flat tire,
might be a tumor,

15:17.369 --> 15:19.569
but it's coming.

15:19.571 --> 15:22.473
So-so what, you're just never
gonna enjoy anything ever again?

15:22.474 --> 15:24.340
Mm, haven't yet.

15:25.510 --> 15:27.545
"Pride goeth before the fall."

15:27.546 --> 15:31.047
Good times will keep on rolling
as long as I'm miserable.

15:32.551 --> 15:34.518
Okay...

15:34.519 --> 15:36.186
Okay.

15:36.187 --> 15:38.721
I know what's going on here.

15:40.392 --> 15:42.759
Somebody needs one of
my special stories.

15:42.761 --> 15:45.763
This one's about a little girl

15:45.764 --> 15:48.399
who suffered a lifetime's
worth of misery.

15:48.400 --> 15:51.435
But she's been
punished enough, okay?

15:51.436 --> 15:54.104
The pride didn't cometh
before the fall.

15:54.105 --> 15:58.742
I think the fall wenteth
before the pride.

15:58.743 --> 16:01.010
In the story,
you're the little girl.

16:02.881 --> 16:05.882
You're even worse in person
than you are on the radio.

16:05.884 --> 16:09.252
Really? 'Cause in
here I'm killing it.

16:10.655 --> 16:13.057
♪ ♪

16:13.058 --> 16:16.060
Hey, there you are, Biggs,
just in time for the ceremony.

16:16.061 --> 16:17.094
What ceremony?

16:17.095 --> 16:18.162
Oh, you didn't hear?

16:18.163 --> 16:19.496
You're being honored.

16:19.497 --> 16:22.031
Marksmanship award.

16:22.033 --> 16:25.135
All right,
let's get this over with.

16:25.136 --> 16:27.570
Congratulations.

16:28.773 --> 16:30.441
That was a clean shooting.

16:30.442 --> 16:32.776
That roof was coming at you.

16:32.777 --> 16:34.510
You had no choice.

16:35.246 --> 16:36.914
Congratulations, Moonroof.

16:37.916 --> 16:39.983
All right, everybody
get their shots in.

16:39.985 --> 16:42.620
Oh, should we do that here
or in your car?

16:44.255 --> 16:45.255
That's great.

16:45.256 --> 16:47.257
Everybody's so funny.

16:47.258 --> 16:48.892
All right, look,
I've had enough of this.

16:48.893 --> 16:49.959
Let's get out of here.

16:49.961 --> 16:52.329
Uh, don't take this
the wrong way, Biggs,

16:52.330 --> 16:53.964
but I already talked
to the captain.

16:53.965 --> 16:55.866
I'm not riding with you anymore.

16:55.867 --> 16:57.368
What are you talking about?
It was an accident.

16:57.369 --> 16:59.637
I told you we should have kept
the shotgun in the trunk.

16:59.638 --> 17:00.838
You tell her, Moonroof.

17:00.839 --> 17:03.974
Shut up.

17:03.975 --> 17:05.709
Look, Biggs, out there
I need a partner

17:05.710 --> 17:09.212
who's gonna watch my back, not
accidentally shoot me in it.

17:09.214 --> 17:12.248
Fine.
Don't be my partner.

17:12.250 --> 17:14.351
I'm sure I can find someone
who'll ride with me.

17:14.352 --> 17:15.652
Really?

17:15.654 --> 17:19.321
Show of hands... who wants
to ride shotgun with Biggs?

17:22.193 --> 17:24.527
I will.

17:24.529 --> 17:26.896
Carl, you-you don't
have to do this.

17:26.897 --> 17:29.600
Just let me talk.

17:29.601 --> 17:32.403
This man
is the best cop in here.

17:32.404 --> 17:34.505
Maybe not by the standards
of physical fitness

17:34.506 --> 17:37.608
or personal hygiene.

17:37.609 --> 17:39.176
But when you talk about heart,

17:39.177 --> 17:42.011
integrity, loyalty...

17:42.013 --> 17:45.215
there's no better partner.

17:45.216 --> 17:48.084
I can think of one.

17:49.421 --> 17:50.921
We had some good times, huh?

17:50.922 --> 17:52.423
Great times.

17:52.424 --> 17:53.857
You really want to try it again?

17:53.858 --> 17:55.692
We're gonna have to go
to couples' counseling.

17:57.195 --> 17:59.730
I'm okay with that.

17:59.731 --> 18:01.497
What made you change your mind?

18:01.499 --> 18:04.934
Been riding around with
Mississippi Burning all day.

18:08.707 --> 18:09.907
I get it.

18:09.908 --> 18:11.608
Mine's got something
against cookies.

18:11.609 --> 18:14.143
Boy, there's a lot
of hate in the world.

18:22.832 --> 18:24.765
♪ ♪

18:24.767 --> 18:28.403
This is <i> Author's
Notes</i> with Robert Castle.

18:28.404 --> 18:30.505
I'm Robert Castle.

18:30.506 --> 18:33.275
With us today are Molly Flynn

18:33.276 --> 18:34.609
and Peggy Biggs,

18:34.611 --> 18:36.678
the co-authors
of the devastating memoir

18:36.679 --> 18:39.046
<i>Under the Shadow
of the Mountain.</i>

18:39.048 --> 18:41.816
Our pleasure, Robert.

18:42.952 --> 18:44.485
Why are you talking like that?

18:44.487 --> 18:46.755
I don't know.
It just happens.

18:46.756 --> 18:49.057
So, about the book.

18:49.058 --> 18:51.293
I think what I found
most powerful

18:51.294 --> 18:54.495
were the feminist themes
you touched on.

18:54.497 --> 18:56.732
I don't know what
that's NPR code for,

18:56.733 --> 18:58.232
but we both like men.

18:58.234 --> 19:00.869
Hey, while we're
here, how the hell

19:00.870 --> 19:02.336
do I get off your pledge list?

19:02.338 --> 19:04.373
I gave five bucks
eight years ago

19:04.374 --> 19:05.807
because I liked your tote bag.

19:05.808 --> 19:07.708
You've been hounding me
ever since.

19:07.710 --> 19:11.613
That's more a question
for our subscription department.

19:11.614 --> 19:13.347
Well, if they're listening,

19:13.349 --> 19:15.549
take me off your damn list.

19:15.551 --> 19:18.086
I know where
your offices are now.

19:18.087 --> 19:20.222
It'd be a shame if something
happened to all them

19:20.223 --> 19:23.258
commie electric cars
parked out front.

19:24.694 --> 19:27.161
<i> Under the Shadow
of the Mountain</i> is available

19:27.163 --> 19:28.997
anywhere that books are sold.

19:28.998 --> 19:31.466
I remember buying my first book.

19:31.467 --> 19:33.835
I, uh, I guess
I've always been attracted

19:33.836 --> 19:36.038
to the written word.
If-if there were books,

19:36.039 --> 19:38.040
I was a-readin', and if, uh...

19:38.041 --> 19:40.642
I'm sorry,
what was your question?

19:40.643 --> 19:42.277
I didn't ask one.

19:42.278 --> 19:43.725
Wonderful.

